TO AUTOMATE SELECTING ALL CHECKBOXES IN A PAGE DOM AND SAVE THE STATE ON CLICK OF A SAVE BUTTON IN JAVASCRIPT, YOU CAN FOLLOW THESE STEPS:

1. FIRST, ADD A SAVE BUTTON TO YOUR HTML.
2. USE JQUERY OR PURE JAVASCRIPT TO SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES AND HANDLE THE CLICK EVENT FOR THE SAVE BUTTON.

HERE IS AN EXAMPLE USING JQUERY:

```HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Checkbox Automation</title>
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <button id="saveButton">Save</button>
    <div>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option1"> Option 1<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option2"> Option 2<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option3"> Option 3<br>
    </div>

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('#saveButton').click(function() {
                // SELECT ALL CHECKBOXES AND LOOP THROUGH THEM
                $('input[type="checkbox"]').each(function() {
                    // SET THE CHECKED PROPERTY BASED ON ITS CURRENT STATE
                    $(this).prop('checked', !$(this).prop('checked'));
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

AND HERE IS AN EXAMPLE USING PURE JAVASCRIPT:

```HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Checkbox Automation</title>
</head>
<body>
    <button id="saveButton">Save</button>
    <div>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option1"> Option 1<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option2"> Option 2<br>
        <input type="checkbox" name="option3"> Option 3<br>
    </div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('saveButton').addEventListener('click', function() {
            var checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

            checkboxes.forEach(function(checkbox) {
                checkbox.checked = !checkbox.checked;
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

IN BOTH EXAMPLES, WHEN YOU CLICK THE "SAVE" BUTTON, ALL CHECKBOXES WILL BE Toggled (IF IT WAS CHECKED, IT WILL BE UNCHECKED, AND VICE VERSA).

